		"description": "<p>When you are hit with a melee weapon attack or take damage from a spell, you may immediately use your reaction to fling caustic blood at your attacker in a 10-foot cone. The triggering creature makes a Dexterity saving throw versus your maneuver DC, taking 1d8 + half your bloodblade level (rounded down) acid damage on a failure, or half as much damage on a success. You may use this ability a number of times equal to your proficiency bonus per long rest.</p>",
